    dc:title "A new velvet gecko (Oedura: Diplodactylidae) from Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835381>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835383>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835379>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835387> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835381>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Colour pattern variability and diagnostic features of O. nesos sp. nov., Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory in life: A) O. nesos sp. nov. paratype, adult with regenerated tail, NTM R38576, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory; B) O. nesos sp. nov. paratype, subadult with original tail, NTM R38582, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory; C) O. nesos sp. nov. uncollected specimen, subadult with original tail, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory; D) O. nesos sp. nov. uncollected specimen, adult with regenerated tail, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory; E) O. nesos sp. nov. uncollected specimen, showing yellowish-white supraoculars and incomplete canthal stripe, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory; F) O. nesos sp. nov. uncollected specimen, dorsal view showing tail narrower than head, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory. Photographs: A–B) G. Gillespie; C–F) C. Jolly." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3835381/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835383>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Comparison of adult and juvenile species in the Oedura marmorata complex from the Top End, Northern Territory in life:A) adult O. nesos sp. nov. uncollected specimen, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory; B) juvenile O. nesos sp. nov. uncollected specimen, Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory; C) adult O. bella sp. nov. uncollected specimen, Caranbirini Conservation Reserve, Northern Territory; D) juvenile O. bella sp. nov. uncollected specimen, Caranbirini Conservation Reserve, Northern Territory; E) adult O. marmorata, uncollected specimen, Wongalara Station, Northern Territory; F) juvenile uncollected specimen, Litchfield National Park, Northern Territory. Photographs: A–B) C. Jolly; C) J. Mulder; D) S. Nielsen; E) S. Zozaya; F) M. Clancy." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3835383/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835379>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A) Summary tree for species in the Oedura marmorata group from the Australian Monsoonal Tropics. Maximum likelihood tree derived from analyses of genomic dataset presented in Skipwith et al. (2019). B) Distribution data of the four recognised species in the Oedura marmorata complex in northern Australia. Species dots correspond to museum records." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3835379/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3835387>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Sandstone escarpment habitat of Oedura nesos sp. nov. on Groote Eylandt, Northern Territory. Photograph: S. Cameron." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3835387/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

